No...

43
00:04:27,477 --> 00:04:30,480
<i>Right now, I'm in no position
to be punishing criminals.</i>

44
00:04:31,731 --> 00:04:33,983
<i>Misa, punish them for me.</i>

45
00:04:38,654 --> 00:04:41,783
<i>Misa. ..
Let's make a new world together.</i>

46
00:05:04,972 --> 00:05:07,725
<i>Be. . .careful.</i>

47
00:05:08,851 --> 00:05:12,814
<i>God. . .is watching.</i>

48
00:05:13,397 --> 00:05:21,489
<i>Please hold my hand...
In the dark alley.</i>

49
00:05:22,031 --> 00:05:25,743
<i>Even if I'm alone
and far away...</i>

50
00:05:26,202 --> 00:05:32,041
<i>You'll always. . .
find me...</i>

51
00:05:32,708 --> 00:05:40,049
<i>You tell me...
everything you know.</i>

52
00:05:41,259 --> 00:05:45,721
<i>Even if. . .
I don't remember...</i>

53
00:05:45,888 --> 00:05:48,891
<i>You tell me...</i>

54
00:05:50,142 --> 00:05:55,064
<i>many times.</i>

55
00:05:59,193 --> 00:06:02,488
<i>But what do I do...</i>

56
00:06:02,572 --> 00:06:11,747
<i>once I know everything?</i>

57
00:06:19,797 --> 00:06:20,798
What's going on?

58
00:06:21,716 --> 00:06:23,301
The murders of criminals have
begun again?

59
00:06:23,968 --> 00:06:25,469
There were sixteen
just yesterday.

60
00:06:26,095 --> 00:06:28,055
They were broadcast after
Higuchi died...

61
00:06:28,764 --> 00:06:30,057
That's thorough, isn't it?

62
00:06:30,725 --> 00:06:33,811
I guess that means that Higuchi
wasn't necessarily Kira...

63
00:06:34,478 --> 00:06:36,314
No. We're positive that

64
00:06:36,397 --> 00:06:38,941
Higuchi was the one killing criminals
until we caught him.

65
00:06:39,358 --> 00:06:42,069
Then does that mean that
another Kira has appeared?

66
00:06:42,904 --> 00:06:45,448
Why?!

67
00:06:45,615 --> 00:06:47,408
Damn it...curse Kira...

68
00:06:48,492 --> 00:06:51,329
<i>Kira appears now...
What's going on?</i>

69
00:06:52,747 --> 00:06:54,123
<i>What is going on?</i>

70
00:06:55,458 --> 00:06:56,792
<i>There's only Misa...</i>

71
00:06:57,877 --> 00:07:00,087
This happened as soon as
Misa was freed, didn't it?

72
00:07:00,546 --> 00:07:04,508
Ryuzaki, are you still saying that?
Misa is not involved.

73
00:07:05,384 --> 00:07:07,803
It happened as soon as Higuchi died.

74
00:07:08,763 --> 00:07:09,805
You're right...

75
00:07:11,974 --> 00:07:16,812
Well, if there is another notebook
and someone is using it...

76
00:07:19,065 --> 00:07:21,150
I'll catch him.

77
00:07:27,990 --> 00:07:30,159
<i>The Shinigami said
it didn't know, but...</i>

78
00:07:31,118 --> 00:07:35,164
<i>If someone could kill by writing a name
on a clipping from the notebook...</i>

79
00:07:38,793 --> 00:07:39,835
<i>It's not impossible...</i>

80
00:07:40,962 --> 00:07:44,382
<i>But. . whoever writes
a name in this notebook...</i>

81
00:07:44,966 --> 00:07:48,052
<i>Has to write another name
within thirteen days or die...</i>

82
00:07:49,679 --> 00:07:52,223
<i>Light Yagami and
Misa Amane are alive...</i>

83
00:07:53,641 --> 00:07:56,686
<i>Thirteen days...
This is the only...</i>

84
00:07:58,813 --> 00:08:02,858
Ryuzaki, even if we do catch the person
who was writing in the notebook...

85
00:08:03,526 --> 00:08:07,321
Can we really convict and punish him
as a serial killer?

86
00:08:07,989 --> 00:08:10,616
Well, of course!

87
00:08:10,783 --> 00:08:14,537
He wrote countless names knowing
that people would die.

88
00:08:14,870 --> 00:08:16,414
We should kill him

89
00:08:16,497 --> 00:08:19,000
if we don't want the existence
of the notebook to go public.

90
00:08:19,959 --> 00:08:21,836
Killing him is harsh,

91
00:08:22,253 --> 00:08:24,755
but I bet that's what our superiors
would demand.

92
00:08:25,715 --> 00:08:28,718
If he admits to killing with
the notebook, he'd get the death penalty.

93
00:08:28,801 --> 00:08:30,386
Or at least a life sentence.

94
00:08:32,680 --> 00:08:34,056
Something like that.

95
00:08:35,016 --> 00:08:37,560
<i>What are you thinking,
Light Yagami?</i>

96
00:08:38,477 --> 00:08:40,563
<i>If Misa is caught,
you'll also be...</i>

97
00:08:43,107 --> 00:08:44,567
<i>So that's it!</i>

98
00:08:45,651 --> 00:08:47,028
<i>You bastard!</i>

99
00:08:49,238 --> 00:08:54,410
<i>Light Yagami is sure that
I'll save Misa's life.</i>

100
00:08:55,077 --> 00:08:57,121
<i>In order to save Misa
in this situation</i>

101
00:08:57,538 --> 00:09:01,542
<i>I'll have to write
Ryuzaki's real name in my notebook.</i>

102
00:09:02,543 --> 00:09:05,087
<i>And if I kill Ryuzaki...</i>

103
00:09:07,381 --> 00:09:11,927
<i>It will definitely affect
Misa's lifespan and I'll die as well...</i>

104
00:09:12,595 --> 00:09:16,390
<i>Light Yagami is making
everything go his way...</i>

105
00:09:19,602 --> 00:09:20,770
<i>What are you going to do, Rem?</i>

106
00:09:21,312 --> 00:09:23,564
<i>I know completely that
despite being a Shinigami,</i>

107
00:09:23,647 --> 00:09:25,691
<i>you care deeply about Misa.</i>

108
00:09:27,109 --> 00:09:31,363
<i>Misa's life has been halved.
There's no way you'd abandon her.</i>

109
00:09:32,239 --> 00:09:34,241
<i>Think about Misa's happiness.</i>

110
00:10:35,719 --> 00:10:38,097
What are you doing there, Ryuzaki?

111
00:10:43,602 --> 00:10:46,355
What are you doing there, Ryuzaki?!

112
00:10:59,410 --> 00:11:00,828
What are you doing, Ryuzaki?

113
00:11:01,871 --> 00:11:04,874
Well, I'm not doing
anything in particular, but...

114
00:11:06,542 --> 00:11:07,751
The sound of bells...

115
00:11:08,711 --> 00:11:09,795
Bells...?

116
00:11:10,629 --> 00:11:11,755
Yes.

117
00:11:12,006 --> 00:11:14,842
The bells have been
really noisy today...

118
00:11:19,263 --> 00:11:20,389
I don't hear anything.

119
00:11:21,724 --> 00:11:22,766
Really?

120
00:11:23,434 --> 00:11:25,394
They've been ringing
all day and...

121
00:11:26,020 --> 00:11:28,105
I can't help but feel curious...

122
00:11:29,273 --> 00:11:31,817
Do you suppose it's a church?
A wedding?

123
00:11:32,651 --> 00:11:33,736
Or, perhaps...

124
00:11:33,819 --> 00:11:35,237
What are you talking about, Ryuzaki?

125
00:11:35,905 --> 00:11:38,032
Don't say such silly things.
Let's go back.

126
00:11:40,034 --> 00:11:41,076
I'm sorry.

127
00:11:42,328 --> 00:11:44,747
Everything I say is
complete nonsense, so...

128
00:11:45,456 --> 00:11:46,916
please, don't believe any of it.

129
00:11:56,508 --> 00:11:57,593
That's right, Ryuzaki.

130
00:11:58,594 --> 00:12:00,971
Most of what you say is nonsense.

131
00:12:01,639 --> 00:12:03,974
There would be no end if
I took you seriously all the time.

132
00:12:04,850 --> 00:12:06,936
I know that the best.

133
00:12:08,354 --> 00:12:11,106
Yes, that's right, Light.

134
00:12:13,609 --> 00:12:16,612
But. . .it's true for both of us.

135
00:12:18,906 --> 00:12:19,990
What do you mean?

136
00:12:22,117 --> 00:12:26,664
Have you ever told the truth
at any point since you were born?

137
00:12:33,462 --> 00:12:34,964
What are you talking about, Ryuzaki?

138
00:12:36,006 --> 00:12:37,883
It's true, I lie once in a while.

139
00:12:39,093 --> 00:12:41,428
But. . .how many people live
their entire lives

140
00:12:41,512 --> 00:12:44,306
only telling the truth?

141
00:12:45,557 --> 00:12:48,143
Humans aren't perfect.

142
00:12:48,852 --> 00:12:50,187
Everyone lies.

143
00:12:51,105 --> 00:12:52,189
Even so...

144
00:12:52,606 --> 00:12:56,318
I've been careful not to
tell lies that hurt others.

145
00:12:57,236 --> 00:12:58,320
That's my answer.

146
00:13:02,491 --> 00:13:03,867
I thought you'd say that.

147
00:13:08,664 --> 00:13:11,083
Let's go back. We're drenched.

148
00:13:12,668 --> 00:13:13,711
Yeah.

149
00:13:24,680 --> 00:13:27,099
Well, that was awful!

150
00:13:27,808 --> 00:13:30,686
It's your fault.
You were standing in that rain.

151
00:13:31,854 --> 00:13:33,981
You're right. I'm sorry.

152
00:13:42,489 --> 00:13:43,741
What are you doing, Ryuzaki?

153
00:13:44,408 --> 00:13:45,701
I thought I'd help you...

154
00:13:46,243 --> 00:13:47,995
Since you're enthusiastically
drying yourself off...

155
00:13:48,620 --> 00:13:50,497
You don't have to do that.

156
00:13:51,040 --> 00:13:52,499
I can give you a massage as well.

157
00:13:53,125 --> 00:13:54,918
It's the least I can do to atone.

158
00:13:55,502 --> 00:13:57,504
I'm pretty good at it.

159
00:13:59,256 --> 00:14:00,299
Do as you please.

160
00:14:00,883 --> 00:14:01,967
All right.

161
00:14:09,558 --> 00:14:10,559
Hey...

162
00:14:10,642 --> 00:14:11,727
You'll get used to it.

163
00:14:22,029 --> 00:14:23,072
You're still wet.

164
00:14:26,909 --> 00:14:27,951
I'm sorry.

165
00:14:51,100 --> 00:14:52,142
It's sad...

166
00:14:52,935 --> 00:14:53,977
What?

167
00:14:56,438 --> 00:14:57,731
We'll soon part ways.

168
00:15:06,323 --> 00:15:07,324
Yes?

169
00:15:09,868 --> 00:15:11,620
All right. I'll come immediately.

170
00:15:16,375 --> 00:15:18,001
Let's go, Light.

171
00:15:18,961 --> 00:15:20,546
It seems it went well.

172
00:15:31,640 --> 00:15:34,268
Oh, Ryuzaki!
What is the meaning of this?!

173
00:15:34,726 --> 00:15:36,562
I heard that you got approval
from another country

174
00:15:36,645 --> 00:15:38,021
to use the notebook
for an execution!

175
00:15:38,772 --> 00:15:40,816
Watari... Good job.

176
00:15:41,191 --> 00:15:42,234
<i>Not at all.</i>

177
00:15:42,317 --> 00:15:43,360
I know it's sudden, but let's...

178
00:15:43,777 --> 00:15:46,113
make arrangements to
transport the notebook.

179
00:15:46,697 --> 00:15:47,698
<i>Yes.</i>

180
00:15:47,781 --> 00:15:49,616
Ryuzaki, what's the meaning of this?

181
00:15:50,909 --> 00:15:53,036
It means that I'm going to
try out the notebook for real.

182
00:15:55,873 --> 00:15:58,000
That's pointless!
We don't have to do that at this point!

183
00:15:58,500 --> 00:16:00,502
We already know that the power
of the notebook is real, don't we?

184
00:16:00,836 --> 00:16:03,213
Besides, who's going to
write the name?

185
00:16:03,338 --> 00:16:04,381
Once you write in the notebook

186
00:16:04,506 --> 00:16:08,385
you have to continue writing names
every thirteen days forever!

187
00:16:09,136 --> 00:16:11,054
The one who's going to write
the name

188
00:16:11,346 --> 00:16:15,017
is someone who'll be executed
within thirteen days.

189
00:16:15,267 --> 00:16:17,060
If he's still alive after thirteen days...

190
00:16:17,728 --> 00:16:20,355
we've made a deal
to commute his execution.

191
00:16:21,523 --> 00:16:23,275
But we can't sacrifice people's lives...

192
00:16:23,358 --> 00:16:24,610
Just a little more.

193
00:16:25,402 --> 00:16:26,695
If we just clear this...

194
00:16:27,029 --> 00:16:28,906
the case will be solved.

195
00:16:34,244 --> 00:16:35,370
W-What's this?!

196
00:16:35,496 --> 00:16:36,580
A blackout?!

197
00:16:47,424 --> 00:16:48,509
<i>Watari?</i>

198
00:16:50,677 --> 00:16:51,762
<i>Watari!</i>

199
00:16:55,557 --> 00:16:57,684
Data deletion?
What's the meaning of this?!

200
00:16:58,685 --> 00:17:01,396
I told Watari to erase all information...

201
00:17:01,480 --> 00:17:05,234
in the event that something
happened to him.

202
00:17:05,984 --> 00:17:07,402
If something happened?

203
00:17:07,903 --> 00:17:08,904
Could it be?!

204
00:17:09,530 --> 00:17:10,531
Where's the Shinigami?

205
00:17:10,614 --> 00:17:12,199
Come to think of it, I don't see it...

206
00:17:14,618 --> 00:17:15,702
It's not here!

207
00:17:16,078 --> 00:17:17,120
What's the meaning of this?!

208
00:17:17,496 --> 00:17:19,164
Everyone...
The Shiniga-!

209
00:17:50,279 --> 00:17:52,489
Ryuzaki! What's wrong?!

210
00:18:57,512 --> 00:18:59,306
Hey! Ryuzaki!

211
00:18:59,848 --> 00:19:01,933
What's wrong?!
Get a hold of yourself!

212
00:19:02,017 --> 00:19:03,852
- What happened?!
- What's going on. . .?

213
00:19:07,356 --> 00:19:08,398
Calm down, Light!

214
00:19:08,649 --> 00:19:09,858
We're going to be killed!

215
00:19:09,941 --> 00:19:12,569
Watari, Ryuzaki, we're next!

216
00:19:26,083 --> 00:19:27,209
Damn it!

217
00:19:27,959 --> 00:19:30,170
Where are you, Shinigami?!
Come out!

218
00:19:30,712 --> 00:19:32,047
Light!

219
00:19:32,422 --> 00:19:35,258
You must know something!
Come out!

220
00:19:36,968 --> 00:19:38,303
Let's search as well.

221
00:19:38,679 --> 00:19:39,680
Yes!

222
00:19:39,763 --> 00:19:41,056
Mogi, please take care of him.

223
00:19:41,431 --> 00:19:42,474
Yes.

224
00:20:03,078 --> 00:20:04,121
Everyone, come here.

225
00:20:05,622 --> 00:20:07,082
What is this?

226
00:20:07,332 --> 00:20:08,333
Sand?

227
00:20:08,417 --> 00:20:09,501
What's going on?

228
00:20:10,711 --> 00:20:13,588
Whatever it is... Whatever happened...

229
00:20:15,257 --> 00:20:17,259
I will avenge Ryuzaki...

230
00:20:18,927 --> 00:20:21,847
Solving this case will
be our gift...

231
00:20:22,848 --> 00:20:26,476
to Watari and the other victims...
for all people...

232
00:20:27,853 --> 00:20:28,937
Light...

233
00:20:29,020 --> 00:20:30,313
That's right, Light.

234
00:20:31,189 --> 00:20:34,443
Yeah, but...we're going to be killed.

235
00:20:34,818 --> 00:20:36,903
Isn't that what this means?

236
00:20:37,612 --> 00:20:40,949
Mr. Matsuda, if you're scared of dying,
leave the investigation.

237
00:20:41,783 --> 00:20:44,202
Only people who have chosen to
risk their lives should be here.

238
00:20:44,786 --> 00:20:46,705
Oh...no. That's right, but...

239
00:20:47,205 --> 00:20:50,876
Light, don't talk like Ryuzaki...

240
00:21:06,475 --> 00:21:08,685
<i>Everyone in my way is gone...</i>

241
00:21:16,651 --> 00:21:20,155
<i>I'm the god of the new world.</i>

242
00:21:22,157 --> 00:21:26,203
TO BE CONTINUED

243
00:21:40,801 --> 00:21:42,677
<i>This single page Forever depressing</i>

244
00:21:43,303 --> 00:21:45,055
<i>A fleeting tactic in the eyes</i>

245
00:21:46,097 --> 00:21:49,810
<i>Without petition evil against the law
